132 |journal=Diplomatic History |volume=39 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=MacDowell |first=Lillian Ione Rhoades |title=The Story of Philadelphia |year=1900 |url=https://archive.org/details/storyphiladelph00macdgoog |page=[https://archive.org/details/storyphiladelph00macdgoog/page/n321 315] |publisher=American Book Company |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Mahan |first=A.T. |title=The Negotiations at Ghent in 1814 |year=1905 |pages=60\u201387 |journal=The American Historical Review |volume=11 |issue=1 |jstor=1832365 |doi=10.2307/1832365 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|first=Thomas|last= Malcomson|title=Freedom by reaching the Wooden World: American Slaves and the British Navy during the War of 1812 |journal=The Northern Mariner|volume= XXII|number= 4 |year=2012|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Millett |first=Nathaniel |title=The Maroons of Prospect Bluff and Their Quest for Freedom in the Atlantic World |year=2013 |publisher=University Press of Florida |isbn=9780813044545 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Mills |first=Dudley |title=The Duke of Wellington and the Peace Negotiations at Ghent in 1814 |year=1921 |pages=19\u201332 |journal=Canadian Historical Review |volume=2 |issue=1 |doi=10.3138/CHR-02-01-02 |url=http://utpjournals.metapress.com/content/h536227283689270/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130128165035/http://utpjournals.metapress.com/content/h536227283689270/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=January 28, 2013 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Morison |first=E. |title=The Maritime History of Massachusetts, 1783\u20131860'' |year=1941 |publisher=Houghton Mifflin Co |isbn=0-9728155-6-2 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Mowat |first=C. L. |title=A Study of Bias in British and American History Textbooks |date=1965 |page=35 |authorlink=C. L. Mowat |journal=Bulletin |publisher=British Association For American Studies |volume=10 |issue=31 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Nettels|first=Curtis P.|title=The Emergence of a National Economy, 1775\u20131815|url=https: