ert |year =2006 |title =Guidebook to the historic sites of the War of 1812 |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UmbQbOcdKngC&pg=PP1|publisher=Dundurn |isbn=1-55002-626-7}}\n* Hickey, Donald R. ''The War of 1812: A Forgotten Conflict'' (1989); abridged as ''The War of 1812: A Short History'' (1995)\n* Hickey, Donald R. ''Don't Give Up the Ship!: Myths of the War of 1812'' (2006)\n* {{cite journal |last=Hickey |first=Donald R |date=Sep 2013 |title=1812: The Old History and the New |journal=Reviews in American History |volume=41 |issue=3 |pages=436\u2013444 |doi=10.1353/rah.2013.0081}}\n* Hickey, Donald R. and Connie D. Clark, eds. ''The Routledge Handbook of the War of 1812'' (2015) 336 pages\n* Jensen, Richard. [http://www.americanhistoryprojects.com/downloads/JMH1812.PDF \"Military history on the electronic frontier: Wikipedia fights the War of 1812.\"] ''Journal of Military History'' 76.4 (2012): 523\u2013556\n* {{Cite book |last=Malcomson |first=Robert |title=Historical Dictionary of the War of 1812 |location=Landham, Maryland |publisher=Scarecrow}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Perkins |first=Bradford |title=Prologue to war: England and the United States, 1805\u20131812 |year=1961 |url=http://www.ucpress.edu/op.php?isbn=9780520009967 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121203215517/http://www.ucpress.edu/op.php?isbn=9780520009967 |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 3, 2012 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Randall |first=William Sterne |title=Unshackling America: How the War of 1812 Truly Ended the American Revolution |publisher=St. Martin's Press |year=2017 |isbn=978-1-2501-1184-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JgumDQAAQBAJ&vq=decatur}}\n* Sapio, Victor. ''Pennsylvania and the War of 1812'' (University Press of Kentucky, 2015).\n* Smith, Gene Allen. ''The Slaves' Gamble: Choosing Sides in the War of 1812.'' New York: Palgrave Macmillan, 2013.\n* {{Cite journal |last=Smith |first=Joshua M. |title=The Yankee Soldier's Might: The District of Maine and the Reputation of the Massachusetts Militia, 1800\u20131812 |journal=New England Quarterly |volume=LXXXIV |date=June 2011 |pages=234\u2013264 |issue=2 |doi=10.1162/tneq_a_00088}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Stacey |first=CP |contribution=The War of 1812 in Canadian History |editor-last=Zaslow |editor2-last=Morris |editor3-last=Turner |editor3-first=Wesley B |year=1964 |title=The Defended Border: Upper Canada and the War of 1812 |location=Toronto}}\n* {{Cite book |last= Stagg |first=J.C.A. |title=The War of 1812: Conflict for a Continent |series=Cambridge Essential Histories |year=2012 |isbn=978-0-521-72686-3}}\n* {{cite book |last=Suthren |first=Victor |title=The War of 1812 |year=1999 |isbn= 0-7710-8317-3}}\n* {{cite book |last=Tanner |first=Helen H. |title=Atlas of Great Lakes Indian History |url=https://archive.org/details/nby_e78_g7_a87_1987 |year=1987|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press |isbn=0-8061-2056-8 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Watts |first=Steven |title=The Republic Reborn: War and the Making of Liberal America, 1790\u20131820 |year=1987  |publisher=The Johns Hopkins University Press |location=Baltimore |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F7yLuSZ0ww8C&pg=PR1 |isbn=0-8018-3420-1 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Williams |first=William Appleman |title=The Contours of American History |year=1961 |publisher=W.W. Norton |isbn=0-393-30561-9 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Wilson |first=Major L. |title=Space, Time, and Freedom: The Quest for Nationality and the Irrepressible Conflict, 1815\u20131861 |year=1974 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n<!--Any links that have not been cited in the article, but related to the article subject area-->\n<!--======================== {{No more links}} ============================\n    | PLEASE BE CAUTIOUS IN ADDING MORE LINKS TO THIS ARTICLE. Wikipedia  |\n    | is not a collection of links nor should it be used for advertising. |\n    |                                                                     |\n    | Excessive or inappropriate links WILL B