{"title_page": "Cornish Shrimper 19", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2019}}\n{{short description|Sailboat class}}\n{{Infobox sailboat specifications \n|name              = Cornish Shrimper 19\n|class_image     = \n|line drawing      = \n|line size         = \n|line alt          = \n|line caption      = \n|image boat        = File:Cornish Shrimper 19 sailboat Starfish 3825.jpg\n|image size        = \n|image alt         = \n|image caption     = \n\n|designer          = [[Roger Dongray]]\n|location          = [[United Kingdom]]\n|year              = 1979\n|no built          = more than 1100\n|design            = \n|class             = \n|brand             = \n|builder           = [[Cornish Crabbers]]\n|role              = \n\n|boats             = \n|crew              = \n|trapeze           = \n|draft             = {{convert|4.00|ft|m|abbr=on}} with [[centreboard]] down\n|air draft         = \n|displacement      = {{convert|2348|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}}\n\n|hulls             = \n|hull type         = [[Monohull]]\n|construction      = [[Fiberglass]]\n|loa               = {{convert|19.25|ft|m|abbr=on}}, {{convert|22.5|ft|m|abbr=on}} with the [[bowsprit]]\n|loh               = \n|lwl               = {{convert|17.58|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|beam              = {{convert|7.16|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|hull draft        = \n|hull weight       = \n|engine            = [[Yanmar]] 1GM {{convert|9|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} [[diesel engine]] or [[outboard motor]]\n\n|appendages        = \n|keel type         = stub keel and centreboard\n|ballast           = \n|rudder type       = transom-mounted [[rudder]]\n\n|rigs              = \n|rig type          = [[gaff rig]]\n|I                 = \n|J                 = \n|P                 = \n|E                 = \n|mast length       = \n|rig other         = \n\n|sails             = \n|sailplan          = [[Fractional rig]]ged [[gaff head]] [[sloop]]\n|sailarea main     = \n|sailarea headsail = \n|lp                = \n|sailarea spin     = \n|sailarea gen      = \n|sails other       = \n|sailarea upwind   = \n|sailarea downwind = \n|sailarea total    = {{convert|194.00|sqft|m2|abbr=on}}\n\n|rating            = \n|d-pn              = \n|rya-pn            = \n|phrf              = \n\n|status            = \n|previous          = \n|successor         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Cornish Shrimper 19''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Trailer sailer|trailerable]] [[sailboat]] that was designed by [[Roger Dongray]], inspired by traditional [[shrimp fishery]] boat designs and first built in 1979.<ref name=\"Data\">{{cite web|url = https://sailboatdata.com/sailboat/cornish-shrimper-19|title = Cornish Shrimper 19 sailboat |accessdate = 28 September 2019|last= McArthur| first = Bruce |work = sailboatdata.com|year = 2019|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190928164635/https://sailboatdata.com/sailboat/cornish-shrimper-19|archivedate =28 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url =https://sailboatdata.com/designer/dongray-roger|title = Roger Dongray|accessdate = 28 September 2019|last= McArthur| first = Bruce |work = sailboatdata.com|year = 2019|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190928164634/https://sailboatdata.com/designer/dongray-roger|archivedate =28 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nThe design has been built by [[Cornish Crabbers]] in [[Wadebridge]], [[Cornwall]] in the [[United Kingdom]] since 1979. The company has built more than 1,100 examples of the design and it remains in production.<ref name=\"Data\"/><ref>{{cite web|url =https://sailboatdata.com/builder/cornish-crabbers|title = Cornish Crabbers|accessdate = 28 September 2019|last= McArthur| first = Bruce |work = sailboatdata.com|year = 2019|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190928164638/https://sailboatdata.com/builder/cornish-crabbers |archivedate = 28 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Official\">{{cite web|url = https://www.cornishcrabbers.co.uk/shrimper-series/shrimper-19/|title = Shrimper 19|access-date = 28 September 2019|author=Cornish Crabbers |work = cornishcrabbers.co.uk |year=2019|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190202165523/https://www.cornishcrabbers.co.uk/shrimper-series/shrimper-19/|archivedate = 2 February 2019 }}</ref>\n\n==Design==\n[[File:Cornish Shrimper 19 sailboat Starfish 3749.jpg|thumb|left|Cornish Shrimper 19]]\n[[File:Cornish Shrimper 19 sailboat Starfish cockpit detail 3750.jpg|thumb|left|Cornish Shrimper 19 cockpit]]\nThe Cornish Shrimper 19 is a recreational [[keelboat]], built predominantly of hand-laid, solid [[fiberglass]], with wood trim and wooden spars. It has a [[gaff rig]] [[sloop]] with a wooden [[bowsprit]], a [[plumb stem]], an angled [[Transom (nautical)|transom]], a transom-hung [[rudder]] controlled by a [[tiller]] and a stub [[keel]] with a [[centreboard]]. It displaces {{convert|2348|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\"Data\"/><ref name=\"Official\"/>\n\nThe boat has a draft of {{convert|4.00|ft|m|abbr=on}} with the centreboard extended and {{convert|1.50|ft|m|abbr=on}} with it retracted, allowing ground transportation on a [[Trailer (vehicle)|trailer]].<ref name=\"Data\"/>\n\nThe boat is normally fitted with a well-mounted [[outboard motor]], or optionally with a Japanese [[Yanmar]] 1GM [[diesel engine]] of {{convert|9|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} for docking and maneuvering.<ref name=\"Data\"/>\n\n==Operational history==\nA 2013 review in ''Cruising World'' by Jen Brett, described the design as \"a salty little boat\" and noted \"with a large cockpit, the Shrimper makes an excellent daysailer for a family, and the basic yet comfortable accommodations below allow the boat to be a simple coastal cruiser.\" Of the boat's looks, she wrote, \"you\u2019ll definitely turn heads while sailing through the harbor\".<ref name=\"Brett\">{{cite web|url = https://www.cruisingworld.com/sailboats/cornish-shrimper/|title = Cornish Shrimper|access-date = 28 September 2019|last = Brett|first = Jen|work = Cruising World|date = 15 September 2019|year=|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20171009191139/http://www.cruisingworld.com/sailboats/cornish-shrimper|archivedate = 9 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of sailing boat types]]\n\n'''Similar sailboats'''\n*[[Com-Pac 19]]\n*[[Mariner 19]]\n*[[Nordica 16]]\n*[[Sanibel 18]]\n*[[West Wight Potter 19]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Official website|https://www.cornishcrabbers.co.uk/shrimper-series/shrimper-19/}}\n{{Trailer sailers and Trailer yachts worldwide}}\n[[Category:Keelboats]]\n[[Category:1970s sailboat type designs]]\n[[Category:Trailer sailers]]\n[[Category:Sailing yachts]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2019}}\n{{short description|Sailboat class}}\n{{Infobox sailboat specifications \n|name              = Cornish Shrimper 19\n|class_image     = \n|line drawing      = \n|line size         = \n|line alt          = \n|line caption      = \n|image boat        = File:Cornish Shrimper 19 sailboat Starfish 3825.jpg\n|image size        = \n|image alt         = \n|image caption     = \n\n|designer          = [[Roger Dongray]]\n|location          = [[United Kingdom]]\n|year              = 1979\n|no built          = more than 1100\n|design            = \n|class             = \n|brand             = \n|builder           = [[Cornish Crabbers]]\n|role              = \n\n|boats             = \n|crew              = \n|trapeze           = \n|draft             = {{convert|4.00|ft|m|abbr=on}} with [[centreboard]] down\n|air draft         = \n|displacement      = {{convert|2348|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}}\n\n|hulls             = \n|hull type         = [[Monohull]]\n|construction      = [[Fiberglass]]\n|loa               = {{convert|19.25|ft|m|abbr=on}}, {{convert|22.5|ft|m|abbr=on}} with the [[bowsprit]]\n|loh               = \n|lwl               = {{convert|17.58|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|beam              = {{convert|7.16|ft|m|abbr=on}}\n|hull draft        = \n|h