 \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\" or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = {{unbulleted list|Brooklyn Nine-Nine|Happy Endings|Rutherford Falls|Superstore}}\n| title              = <!-- Formal/awarded/job title. The parameter |office=may be used as an alternative when the label is better rendered as \"Office\" (e.g. public office or appointments) -->\n| spouse             = <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters -->\n| mother             = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| father             = <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| relatives          = \n| family             = \n| awards             = \n| website            = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Sierra Nizhoni Teller Ornelas''' (born 1981)<ref name=\"Schmitt\" /> is a [[Navajo]] and [[Mexican American]] [[showrunner]], [[screenwriter]], [[filmmaker]] and [[Navajo weaving|weaver]] from [[Tucson, Arizona]]. She is the co-creator of the scripted comedy series ''Rutherford Falls'', alongside [[Ed Helms]] and [[Mike Schur]].<ref name=\"Montpelier2019\" /><ref name=\"Tennant\">{{cite news |last1=Tennant |first1=Zoe |title=Rutherford Falls brings Indigenous writers together for new NBC sitcom |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/unreserved/lights-camera-oscars-meet-the-creators-decolonizing-hollywood-1.5450603/rutherford-falls-brings-indigenous-writers-together-for-new-nbc-sitcom-1.5452884 |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=CBC |date=7 February 2020}}</ref> Known for writing and production work on shows such as ''[[Brooklyn Nine-Nine]]'', ''[[Happy Endings (TV series)|Happy Endings]]'', ''[[Splitting Up Together]]'' and ''[[Superstore (TV series)|Superstore]]'', she has written and contributed to ''[[This American Life]]'' and the [[New York Times]].<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\">{{cite news |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |last2=Andreeva |first2=Nellie |title=\u2018Rutherford Falls\u2019 Co-Creator Sierra Teller Ornelas Inks Overall Deal With Universal TV |url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/rutherford-falls-co-creator-sierra-teller-ornelas-inks-overall-deal-with-universal-tv-1202790287/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=Deadline |date=20 November 2019 |language=en}}</ref> In 2019 Ornelas signed a multi-year development deal with Universal Television.<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\" /><ref name=\"Montpelier2019\">{{cite news |last1=Montpelier |first1=Rachel |title=Sierra Teller Ornelas Signs Multi-Year Overall Deal with Universal Television |url=https://womenandhollywood.com/sierra-teller-ornelas-signs-multi-year-overall-deal-with-universal-television/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=womenandhollywood.com |date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nOrnelas is from Tucson, Arizona.<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\" /><ref name=\"Harjo\">{{cite news |last1=Harjo |first1=Noetta |title=GGA Indigenerd Wire: Sierra Teller Ornelas Talks Authenticity and Humor in Native Storytelling |url=https://www.geekgirlauthority.com/indigenerd-wire-sierra-teller-ornelas-native-storytelling/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=Geek Girl Authority |date=17 September 2018}}</ref> Born to the Edge Water clan, her maternal grandfather is Water Flowing Together clan and her paternal grandfather is Mexican clan.<ref name=\"Ornelas\">{{cite news |last1=Ornelas |first1=Sierra Teller |title=Indigenous People's Long Road to Visibility in Hollywood (Guest Column) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/indigenous-peoples-long-road-visibility-hollywood-guest-column-1180631 |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=30 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> She attended the [[University of Arizona]], where she studied media arts.<ref name=\"AirzonaDailyWeaving\">{{cite news |title=Weaving is part of woman's soul |url=https://tucson.com/news/foreign-language/spanish/weaving-is-part-of-woman-s-soul/article_3ea99998-b960-59b9-acbc-915462e7e21f.html |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=Arizona Daily Star |date=13 December 2006 |language=en}}</ref> Following graduation she worked for five years as a film programmer at the [[National Museum of the American Indian]] in [[Washington D.C.]].<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\" /><ref name=\"Sussman\">{{cite web |last1=Sussman |first1=Mark |title=Sierra Teller Ornelas on giving yourself permission to suck |url=https://thecreativeindependent.com/people/sierra-teller-ornelas-on-giving-yourself-permission-to-suck/ |website=thecreativeindependent.com |accessdate=9 April 2020 |date=10 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 Ornelas was selected to participate in the Disney/ABC Television Group's diversity writing program.<ref name=\"DisneyWrap\">{{cite news |title=Eight Chosen for Disney/ABC TV Diversity Writing Program |url=https://www.thewrap.com/eight-chosen-disneyabc-tv-diversity-writing-program-14389/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=TheWrap |date=18 February 2010}}</ref> Following the end of the program she was asked to continue on as a staff writer on ''[[Happy Endings (TV series)|Happy Endings]]''.<ref name=\"Yurth\">{{cite news |last1=Yurth |first1=Cindy |title=For Din\u00e9 scriptwriter, Hollywood is one big dinner table |url=https://navajotimes.com/entertainment/people/2011/1011/102411ornelas.php |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=navajotimes.com |date=24 October 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Montpelier2018\" /> The position allowed her to contribute to a sub-plot in which Dave, played by [[Zachary Knighton]], discovers he is one-sixteenth Navajo and begins playing into stereotypes about Native Americans.<ref name=\"Yurth\" /><ref name=\"Montpelier2018\">{{cite news |last1=Montpelier |first1=Rachel |title=Writer to Watch: Sierra Teller Ornelas of \"Superstore\" |url=https://womenandhollywood.com/writer-to-watch-sierra-teller-ornelas-of-superstore/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=womenandhollywood.com |date=14 September 2018}}</ref> Ornelas explained in a 2011 interview with the ''[[Navajo Times]]'' that if done right, comedy can be a way to \"get conversation going about very dense, complicated issues.\"<ref name=\"Yurth\" />\n\nDiversity in writers' rooms and ensuring that racialized people aren't the only one working on a production is an area Ornelas is committed to addressing in media.<ref name=\"Montpelier2018\" /> As the showrunner of ''Rutherford Falls'' she oversees a writers room that includes herself, Helms, Schur and four other Indigenous writers - Tazbah Chavez, Tai Leclaire, Jana Schmieding, and Bobby Wilson - the number of which is believed to be a first for a major television production.<ref name=\"Tennant\" />\n\nIn addition to writing and producing, Ornelas is an award-winning sixth-generation Navajo weaver.<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\" /><ref name=\"AirzonaDailyWeaving\" /> Her film ''A Loom With a View: Modern Navajo Weavers'', made for the [[Arizona State Museum]], chronicles the weaving of her mother, Barbara Teller Ornelas; aunt, Margaret Yazzie; and brother, Micheal Teller Ornelas.<ref name=\"AirzonaDailyWeaving\" /><ref name=\"Schmitt\">{{cite book |last1=Schmitt |first1=Rory O'Neill |title=Navajo and Hopi Art in Arizona: Continuing Traditions |date=2016 |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |isbn=978-1-62585-560-2 |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=AGxBCwAAQBAJ&lpg=PT84&ots=nB5PyxjrZy&dq=%22A%20Loom%20With%20a%20View%22%20ornelas&pg=PT84#v=onepage&q=%22A%20Loom%20With%20a%20View%22%20ornelas&f=false |accessdate=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|1599337}}\n\n[[Category:Navajo people]]\n[[Category:American television writers]]\n[[Category:People from Tucson, Arizona]]\n[[Category:American television producers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Sierra Teller Ornelas\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| image_upright      = \n| landscape          = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth year and age|1981}} \n| birth_place        = [[Tucson, Arizona]]\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (enter DEATH date then BIRTH date (e.g., ...|1908|31|8|1967|28|2}} use both this parameter and |birth_date to display the person's date of birth, date of death, and age at death) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       = <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| siglum             = \n| citizenship        = \n| education          = University of Arizona \n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent = <!-- Discouraged in most cases, specifically when promotional, and requiring a reliable source -->\n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = <!-- produces label \"Notable work\"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label \"Notable credit(s)\"; or by |works=, which produces label \"Work