ollywood (Guest Column) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/indigenous-peoples-long-road-visibility-hollywood-guest-column-1180631 |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=30 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> She attended the [[University of Arizona]], where she studied media arts.<ref name=\"AirzonaDailyWeaving\">{{cite news |title=Weaving is part of woman's soul |url=https://tucson.com/news/foreign-language/spanish/weaving-is-part-of-woman-s-soul/article_3ea99998-b960-59b9-acbc-915462e7e21f.html |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=Arizona Daily Star |date=13 December 2006 |language=en}}</ref> Following graduation she worked for five years as a film programmer at the [[National Museum of the American Indian]] in [[Washington D.C.]].<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\" /><ref name=\"Sussman\">{{cite web |last1=Sussman |first1=Mark |title=Sierra Teller Ornelas on giving yourself permission to suck |url=https://thecreativeindependent.com/people/sierra-teller-ornelas-on-giving-yourself-permission-to-suck/ |website=thecreativeindependent.com |accessdate=9 April 2020 |date=10 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 Ornelas was selected to participate in the Disney/ABC Television Group's diversity writing program.<ref name=\"DisneyWrap\">{{cite news |title=Eight Chosen for Disney/ABC TV Diversity Writing Program |url=https://www.thewrap.com/eight-chosen-disneyabc-tv-diversity-writing-program-14389/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=TheWrap |date=18 February 2010}}</ref> Following the end of the program she was asked to continue on as a staff writer on ''[[Happy Endings (TV series)|Happy Endings]]''.<ref name=\"Yurth\">{{cite news |last1=Yurth |first1=Cindy |title=For Din\u00e9 scriptwriter, Hollywood is one big dinner table |url=https://navajotimes.com/entertainment/people/2011/1011/102411ornelas.php |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=navajotimes.com |date=24 October 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Montpelier2018\" /> The position allowed her to contribute to a sub-plot in which Dave, played by [[Zachary Knighton]], discovers he is one-sixteenth Navajo and begins playing into stereotypes about Native Americans.<ref name=\"Yurth\" /><ref name=\"Montpelier2018\">{{cite news |last1=Montpelier |first1=Rachel |title=Writer to Watch: Sierra Teller Ornelas of \u201cSuperstore\u201d |url=https://womenandhollywood.com/writer-to-watch-sierra-teller-ornelas-of-superstore/ |accessdate=9 April 2020 |work=womenandhollywood.com |date=14 September 2018}}</ref> Ornelas explained in a 2011 interview with the ''[[Navajo Times]]'' that if done right, comedy can be a way to \"get conversation going about very dense, complicated issues.\"<ref name=\"Yurth\" />\n\nDiversity in writers' rooms and ensuring that racialized people aren't the only one working on a production is an area Ornelas is committed to addressing in media.<ref name=\"Montpelier2018\" /> As the showrunner of ''Rutherford Falls'' she oversees a writers room that includes herself, Helms, Schur and four other Indigenous writers - Tazbah Chavez, Tai Leclaire, Jana Schmieding, and Bobby Wilson - the number of which is believed to be a first for a major television production.<ref name=\"Tennant\" /> \n\nIn addition to writing and producing, Ornelas is an award winning sixth-generation Navajo weaver.<ref name=\"PetskiAndreeva\" /><ref name=\"AirzonaDailyWeaving\" /> Her film ''A Loom With a View: Modern Navajo Weavers'', made for the [[Arizona State Museum]], chronicles the weaving of her mother, Barbara Teller Ornelas; aunt, Margaret Yazzie; and brother, Micheal Teller Ornelas.<ref name=\"AirzonaDailyWeaving\" /><ref name=\"Schmitt\">{{cite book |last1=Schmitt |first1=Rory O'Neill |title=Navajo and Hopi Art in Arizona: Continuing Traditions |date=2016 |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |isbn=978-1-62585-560-2 |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=AGxBCwAAQBAJ&lpg=PT84&ots=nB5PyxjrZy&dq=%22A%20Loom%20With%20a%20View%22%20ornelas&pg=PT84#v=onepage&q=%22A%20Loom%20With%20a%20View%22%20ornelas&f=false |accessdate=9 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|1599337}}\n\n[[Category:Navajo people]]\n[[Category:American television writers]]\n[[Category:People from Tucson, Arizona]]\n[[Category:American television producers]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up,typo(s) fixed: award winning \u2192 award-winning", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sierra_Teller_Ornelas"}
